main event: Multiple sightings of bright, fast-moving objects were reported in different locations in Australia and the United States between May 1953 and July 1953.
interesting points: A group of 11 people in Darlington and Monroe, Wisconsin, witnessed a brilliant white light low in the Eastern sky, which later paralleled the course of Venus, leading to the conclusion that it was an Astronomical-Venus event.
RAAF pilot Captain E.L. Jones reported seeing a fast-moving, grayish-brown circular object at 6,000 ft. near Mackay, North Queensland, Australia, which could not be identified.
A meteorological officer in Dri Nimno, Australia, observed a bright crescent-shaped object moving in a southerly direction that appeared suspended in space and reflecting sunlight.
A bright, 100 ft. long circular object was reported in Surrey Hills, Melbourne, that shone brilliantly in the sun for about 4 minutes.
A a bright silver object, larger than a basketball and tilted like a plate, was reported hovering and then taking off at tremendous speed straight up into the sky in Indiana, May 1955.
sighted object: bright, fast-moving, unidentified objects in the sky
location: multiple locations, including Darlington and Monroe, Wisconsin, North Queensland, Dri Nimno, Melbourne, and Indiana
witnesses: multiple credible witnesses, including RAAF pilot, meteorological officers, and groups of people
